<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Airport Operators Association response to Transport Select Committee call for written evidence on Winter Resilience in Transport</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Written evidence from the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Airport Operators Association </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(WRT 036)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Airport Operators Association (AOA) is the national voice of UK airports. We are a trade association representing the interests of UK airports, and the principal such body engaging with the UK Government and regulatory authorities on airport matters. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In recent years, UK airports have taken significant steps – and made major investments in specialist snow clearing equipment – to improve winter resilience. For example, Manchester Airport has invested around £6 million, Aberdeen £1.3 million and Heathrow</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> £32.4 million on new snow fleet equipment and staff. An AOA Snow Planning Survey, conducted in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">winter</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> 2012, shows good practice around UK airports, and is co-signed by AOA and the British Air Transport Association, the trade</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> body of UK airlines, which is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">enclosed below. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We would therefore advise that AOA member airports have a high state of preparedness for the forthcoming winter period. While it is almost inevitable that very severe winter weather will cause disruption to all modes of transport, UK airp</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">orts have:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Effective command and control procedures in place to respond to severe winter incidents;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Effective snow and ice clearing operations for aircraft hard standings, aprons, runways and taxiways;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Resilience of ground de-icing product supplies and ope</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rations;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Provision of outward facing information for air passengers whose flights maybe disrupted;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Agreements with airlines for providing on-site air passengers obliged to wait for delayed flight; and</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.71pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Contingency arrangements in place with airlines, surfac</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e transport providers, hotels, emergency services, local and voluntary services, for ensuring the welfare of passengers whose flights have been delayed or cancelled.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition to the above, you may also wish to note that CAA led a trial during the last </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">winter period concerned with the reporting of runway condition during winter conditions which involved both airports and airlines. Industry is currently awaiting the publication of the results of this trial but we believe that this further demonstrates our</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> desire to continually improve our overall winter resilience.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">AIRPORT OPERATORS ASSOCIATION</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">2012 SNOW PLANNING SURVEY</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">SUMMARY OF FINDINGS</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The UK in recent years has seen increased interest</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> by a number of stakeholders</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in the issue of how civil aviation </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">copes </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with the disruption </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">exceptional weather events can cause. Such exceptional events – such as snow – can impact airports, airlines, surface access transport to airports; and ultimately this affects aviation personnel, freight operations and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, of course,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> passengers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">early </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">201</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2, the CAA asked the aviation sector to produce a brief report which details the work UK aviation conducts to address exceptional weather events like snow. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In response, o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n behalf of the UK airports sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the Airport Operators Association </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(AOA) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has liaise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">d with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a number of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">its network of members to produce the following overview of the positive steps taken by airports in readiness for winter operations.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> In producing the report, AOA has worked with the British Air Transport Association (BATA) and several of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> its member airlines to ensure the findings reflect efforts made not only by airport operators but also by UK airlines. Other stakeholders – including national and local government and their agencies – also have key roles to play in ensuring airport and ai</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rline operations can continue to function during challenging winter weather conditions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Please see in the pages to follow a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> list of examples of the work airports </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and airlines undertake </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to address snow events which can affect their winter operations. When </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reading this document, it is important to bear in mind that there should be no expectation that these activities are being done by all airports or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">airlines or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">indeed are appropriate for all airports </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and airlines </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">– the list merely highlights the work and in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">itiatives undertaken to deal with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">adverse winter weather</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The document details examples of recent changes and good practice conducted by UK airports and airlines in three sections: operational; management; and passenger communications and welfare. Its </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">purpose is to provide an indicative précis of some of the work UK airports and airlines perform where appropriate t to address the impact of snow on winter operations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We thank the following airports for their assistance: Aberdeen, Belfast City, Birmingha</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">m, Blackpool, Bristol, Edinburgh, Exeter, Gatwick, Glasgow, Heathrow, Leeds Bradford, Liverpool, London City, Luton, Manchester, Newcastle, Newquay Cornwall, Norwich, Prestwick, Southampton, and Stansted.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:1pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt; width:482.2pt"><tr><td style="background-color:#000000; border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:2.25pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:129pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="color:#ffffff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">SECTION 1: OPERATIONAL</span></p></td><td style="background-color:#000000; border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:2.25pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:353.2pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#ffffff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">EXAMPLES OF RECENT CHANGES / GOOD PRACTICE</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="background-color:#d2eaf1; border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:129pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Snow vehicles</span></p></td><td style="background-color:#d2eaf1; border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:353.2pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 47.51pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Strong evidence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of purchase of new snow vehicles across airports, including equipment for:</span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 83.35pt; padding-left:6.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Ploughing </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 83.35pt; padding-left:6.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Sweeping </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 83.35pt; padding-left:6.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">De-icing</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 83.35pt; padding-left:6.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Blowing</span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A number of airports reporting up to doubling of fleets (eg. Heathrow increased its available vehicles from 50 in 2010, to 185)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Additional </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">vehicles to allow faster runway clearance (eg. Stansted estimates 17 minute saving, by purchase of additional vehicle)</span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Provision on new accommodation for snow vehicles, including maintenance and storage areas</span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Increased fuel storage for snow clearing vehicl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">es</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Benefits found from small utility vehicles (“Multi-Hogs”) in terms of versatility and effectiveness for clearing stands</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Use of support contracts to provide additional vehicles at short notice, other than those owned / operated by the airport</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Smaller air</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ports making use of “push powered” snow brushes / blowers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 45.91pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Increased use of lease arrangements to ensure availability of new vehicles</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:129pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Other snow clearing equipment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Other snow clearing equipment</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> – cont.d</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:353.2pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Considerable evidence of purchase of other </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">new snow clearing equipment</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Increased use of hand held snow ploughs, shovels and scoops for more difficult areas</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Increased use of granular (prill) de-icing equipment</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Increased use of “on hire” equipment to provide additional resilience</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 53.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 53.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Use of “snow </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cutters”  to take load off, and increase effectiveness of, snow sweepers, reducing time taken for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">runway clearance</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font