 test response protocols, for example during volcanic a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sh, fog, or industrial action</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:127.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Management processes (for example, triggers that activate parts of snow plan)</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:354.6pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The majority of airports are using triggers, which activate parts of the snow plan, based on weather forecasts of how far into the future snow is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">being forecast. Many airports report relying on the use of Met Office “Open Runway” service for this, rather than more general forecasts of snow fall</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Development of new early warning indicators and escalation triggers – for example, Heathrow has now develo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ped some 40 different categories, including terminal congestion, reduced flight departures and failures in equipment and systems.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td style="background-color:#d2eaf1; border-bottom-color:#4bacc6; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; border-left-color:#4bacc6; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1pt; border-right-color:#4bacc6; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1pt; border-top-color:#4bacc6; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:127.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Internal communications and assessment of situation on ground (for example, new internal commun</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ication processes, increased </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">use of CCTV, or telemetry)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-