l-align:top; width:354.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition to traditional methods such as tannoy, information desks, and deployment of ext</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ra staff giving verbal information, members reported:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A greater emphasis on close liaison </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with airlines to ensure Flight Information Displays (FIDs) can be updated as quickly as possible</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This is achieved, for example, through g</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reater use of text messaging</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (for example, using “Esendex”)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Upgrading of FIDs (using, for example, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Chroma Fusion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> system) to allow for free text to be displayed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> provid</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> more specific messaging</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Deployment of mobile FIDs to provide better and clearer information</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Communications – m</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">dia screens turned to welfare messages</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> if appropriate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">; and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4 hour telephone contact centre</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Equipping additional staff with mobile devices to help them access airport and airline information and convey it to passengers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">More use of television feeds and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">general information screens</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Modification of airport websites to provide clearer and fuller information about weather disruption on front pages</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size: